New Records: Cleveland Cavaliers became the 12th team in NBA history to start a season 11-0 after defeating the Brooklyn Nets 105-100 on November 10, 2024.
Key Match Events: Evan Mobley starred with 23 points and 16 rebounds, while Donovan Mitchell scored 22 points as the Cavaliers secured their 11th consecutive win to start the season.
Post-Match Reflections: The Cavaliers' victory marked a significant milestone in their season, highlighting their strong start and team cohesion.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game featured notable performances and moments, including Darius Garland's late-game scoring and defensive efforts.
